{"questionId":"22818","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The admissions team at a new university are trying to predict the number of student&nbsp;applications they will receive each year.</p>\n<p>Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math> be the number of years that the university has been open. The admissions team collect the following data for the first two years.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/0d0fd473258347545caf6a7a1bfc24be107809cc.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>It is assumed that the number of students that apply to the university each year will follow a&nbsp;geometric sequence, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find an expression for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>u</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>12</mn><mo> </mo><mn>300</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>03</mn><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22818","referenceCode":"21N.2.SL.TZ0.2b.ii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find an expression for un.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.2—Arithmetic sequences and series","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.3—Geometric sequences and series","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.6—Approximating and estimating"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}